==Slovak==
=== Personal Pronoun ===
'''sa''' ''or'' '''[[seba#Slovak|seba]]'''

Replaces the [[accusative]] of any personal pronoun whenever the [[object]], whether expressed or implied, is of the same [[person]] as the [[subject]]. Typically can be translated as the corresponding version of ''oneself'':
:'''vidím sa v zrkadle'''&mdash;''I see myself in the mirror
:'''Koho vidíš v zrkadle? Seba.'''&mdash;''Whom do you see in the mirror? Myself.''

=== Reflexive Pronon ===
'''sa'''

Bound with certain verbs, similar to the Italian [[si#Italian|si]]. The pronoun is a part of the verb. For example, '''modliť sa'''&mdash;''to pray''. There is no '''modliť''' in Slovak without the '''sa'''.